      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you, but it feels like the \"mitigation\" you're talking about is just a way to gloss over the fact that these policies often cause immediate harm to low-income families. Is it really \"balancing\" if the outcome is almost always the displacement of the current community in favor of higher-income newcomers? It seems like the \"benefits\" are mostly for developers and new residents, not the people actually living there now.",
